<paper id="1598342504"><title>Reachability Analysis at Procedure Level through Timing Coincidence</title><year>1995</year><authors><author org="Academia SInica" id="2128555674">Farn Wang</author></authors><n_citation>7</n_citation><doc_type>Conference</doc_type><references><reference>1491178396</reference><reference>1499407607</reference><reference>1501731334</reference><reference>1507695589</reference><reference>1508190831</reference><reference>1524856836</reference><reference>1823037702</reference><reference>1975657455</reference><reference>2056359803</reference><reference>2080267935</reference><reference>2098228838</reference><reference>2117189826</reference><reference>2123410838</reference><reference>2151612633</reference><reference>2153439859</reference><reference>2156289446</reference><reference>2167668895</reference></references><venue id="1145706541" type="C">International Conference on Concurrency Theory</venue><doi>10.1007/3-540-60218-6_21</doi><keywords><keyword weight="0.42664">Discrete mathematics</keyword><keyword weight="0.45019">Computer science</keyword><keyword weight="0.0">Discrete time domain</keyword><keyword weight="0.47627">Thread (computing)</keyword><keyword weight="0.46339">Theoretical computer science</keyword><keyword weight="0.56589">Reachability</keyword><keyword weight="0.48743">Structured programming</keyword><keyword weight="0.43017">Coincidence</keyword><keyword weight="0.49027">Procedure</keyword><keyword weight="0.49053">Recursion</keyword></keywords><publisher>Springer, Berlin, Heidelberg</publisher><abstract>A procedure level model description language compatible with the concept of structured programming is devised for real-time concurrent systems with a global clock of discrete time domain. The complexities of its ID-vector reachability problems, both for recursive and nonrecursive systems, are investigated. A reachability analysis algorithm for nonrecursive systems is then introduced to take advantage of the synchrony among and the autonomy of multiple concurrent threads.</abstract></paper>